00:02:28.539 --> 00:02:29.539
(Workbook 1)

32
00:02:31.509 --> 00:02:34.140
Father, you can't even imagine...

33
00:02:34.140 --> 00:02:35.480
what I've done...

34
00:02:36.409 --> 00:02:38.020
to stay loyal to these people.

35
00:03:07.809 --> 00:03:10.009
Don't ignore what Mr. Byun said...

36
00:03:10.879 --> 00:03:12.279
about June's father.

37
00:03:13.749 --> 00:03:15.120
Why are you also saying that?

38
00:03:16.589 --> 00:03:17.860
I don't care what Woo Sung says.

39
00:03:18.159 --> 00:03:20.020
It's relevant if he thinks it's a problem.

40
00:03:22.029 --> 00:03:24.390
He thinks that June has a grudge against the company.

41
00:03:25.159 --> 00:03:27.430
That's why he's uncomfortable seeing June next to you.

42
00:03:27.529 --> 00:03:29.330
The fact that I like June has nothing to do with him.

43
00:03:30.529 --> 00:03:32.640
You have no idea how scary your brother is.

44
00:03:34.140 --> 00:03:36.240
He does everything it takes to realize his goals.

45
00:03:39.809 --> 00:03:40.839
What do you mean?

46
00:03:49.050 --> 00:03:50.819
Your brother released...

47
00:03:52.390 --> 00:03:53.390
your air rage video.

48
00:03:55.730 --> 00:03:57.289
This is a warning.

49
00:03:58.159 --> 00:04:00.230
He won't let you act up again.

50
00:04:08.740 --> 00:04:09.870
So, Woo Sung...

51
00:04:12.839 --> 00:04:14.110
wants to get rid of me.

52
00:04:17.350 --> 00:04:18.350
Right, Je Hoon?

53
00:04:24.519 --> 00:04:27.259
Why didn't you tell me earlier?

54
00:04:29.629 --> 00:04:33.030
Do you think it was easy for me to tell you this?

55
00:04:35.600 --> 00:04:36.730
It must have been difficult...

56
00:04:38.840 --> 00:04:39.970
for you to keep this to yourself.

57
00:05:36.230 --> 00:05:37.329
It was a nice meal.

58
00:05:38.530 --> 00:05:39.860
It was.

59
00:05:44.870 --> 00:05:45.970
June.

60
00:05:46.639 --> 00:05:47.699
I'm tired.

61
00:05:50.569 --> 00:05:51.639
I'll go inside first.

62
00:05:54.649 --> 00:05:55.649
All right. Go rest.

63
00:06:44.759 --> 00:06:45.829
(My daughter)

64
00:06:48.370 --> 00:06:49.430
Hello?

65
00:06:49.870 --> 00:06:52.800
June, what's going on? You never call me first.

66
00:06:54.870 --> 00:06:57.110
Hello? June?

67
00:07:01.610 --> 00:07:02.610
Yes, Mom.

68
00:07:05.280 --> 00:07:06.319
How are you?

69
00:07:07.780 --> 00:07:09.120
I'm always doing fine.

70
00:07:09.920 --> 00:07:11.220
Is everything all right with you?

71
00:07:13.059 --> 00:07:14.319
It's fine.

72
00:07:15.730 --> 00:07:19.399
I'll visit you in a few days. I made lettuce kimchi that you like.

73
00:07:20.600 --> 00:07:21.629
Gosh, Mom.

74
00:07:22.829 --> 00:07:25.040
It was Dad who liked lettuce kimchi.

75
00:07:27.199 --> 00:07:28.269
Really?

76
00:07:31.379 --> 00:07:32.379
Mom.

77
00:07:36.209 --> 00:07:37.949
What was Dad like?

78
00:07:38.879 --> 00:07:41.149
Why? Is something wrong?

79
00:07:43.319 --> 00:07:44.319
No, just asking.

80
00:07:44.720 --> 00:07:46.819
Why? What's wrong, June?

81
00:07:56.930 --> 00:07:57.939
Did Dad...

82
00:08:01.769 --> 00:08:02.769
really get fired...

83
00:08:03.740 --> 00:08:04.939
from Gangsu Group...

84
00:08:06.240 --> 00:08:07.879
because he was bribed?

85
00:08:09.280 --> 00:08:10.579
What are you talking about?

86
00:08:11.480 --> 00:08:13.680
Who told you that? Where did you hear that?

87
00:08:16.319 --> 00:08:17.350
Gosh.

88
00:08:20.290 --> 00:08:22.360
I'm so upset, Mom.

89
00:08:39.740 --> 00:08:40.740
Poor girl.

90
00:08:42.049 --> 00:08:44.049
According to Mr. Kwon,

91
00:08:44.049 --> 00:08:46.580
the rooftop is an awful place to live in.

92
00:08:48.889 --> 00:08:50.590
She cleans to make her living.

93
00:08:50.919 --> 00:08:52.460
Of course she lives in an awful place.

94
00:08:53.620 --> 00:08:56.830
But still, she's the person who has brought Hyuk to his senses.

95
00:08:57.259 --> 00:09:00.399
Are you just going to leave her to be a cleaner?

96
00:09:01.499 --> 00:09:02.600
What are you saying?

97
00:09:03.129 --> 00:09:06.899
She should be brought to a certain level so that people won't gossip.

98
00:09:08.870 --> 00:09:11.310
She stormed into my room to say everything she wanted to say.

99
00:09:11.509 --> 00:09:13.179
I guess she's no ordinary person.

100
00:09:14.549 --> 00:09:16.909
And she helped Hyuk act like a human being.

101
00:09:17.879 --> 00:09:19.679
She must have a lot to offer too.

102
00:09:20.950 --> 00:09:21.990
Yes, Father.

103
00:09:24.049 --> 00:09:25.389
She does.

104
00:09:27.720 --> 00:09:30.230
Do you know Baek Seung Gi?

105
00:09:31.960 --> 00:09:33.029
Baek Seung Gi?

106
00:09:33.929 --> 00:09:34.970
Who's that?

107
00:09:35.529 --> 00:09:37.499
He was the planning team's manager who created Gangsu gochujang.

108
00:09:38.399 --> 00:09:40.740
Mom told me to find out about her, so I did some digging.

109
00:09:42.310 --> 00:09:43.340
I found out that Baek June...

110
00:09:44.139 --> 00:09:45.409
is Baek Seung Gi's daughter.

111
00:09:46.639 --> 00:09:48.549
Really? She's the daughter of the manager...

112
00:09:49.210 --> 00:09:50.850
that created our gochujang?

113
00:09:51.220 --> 00:09:53.019
Gosh, that's great news.

114
00:09:53.220 --> 00:09:54.620
We don't even need to look any further.

115
00:09:55.320 --> 00:09:58.560
It's a great idea to have someone like that as a daughter-in-law.

116
00:09:58.960 --> 00:09:59.990
Don't you think so too?

117
00:10:00.389 --> 00:10:02.659
That scum. Why did he have to meet a woman like that?

118
00:10:05.230 --> 00:10:06.529
- What? - It's not going to happen.

119
00:10:07.029 --> 00:10:09.929
Pyeongang or not, we're never going to speak of her again.

120
00:10:10.399 --> 00:10:11.600
- Do you understand? - Oh, my.

121
00:10:14.810 --> 00:10:17.740
Gosh, what's wrong with him?

122
00:10:18.509 --> 00:10:21.649
If he created our gochujang, he contributed a lot to the company.

123
00:10:22.149 --> 00:10:23.679
When the company was having a hard time,

124
00:10:24.409 --> 00:10:26.379
it was the gochujang that saved us all.

125
00:10:28.519 --> 00:10:31.889
Anyhow, the fortuneteller told me they were destined to be.

126
00:10:32.659 --> 00:10:34.019
He was right.

127
00:10:34.320 --> 00:10:38.129
Gosh, Mother. Stop visiting the fortuneteller.

128
00:10:38.499 --> 00:10:42.269
Baek June won't save Hyuk. She'll only eat him up.

129
00:10:44.799 --> 00:10:46.070
Eat him up?

130
00:10:46.740 --> 00:10:48.240
What do you mean?

131
00:10:53.379 --> 00:10:56.149
I'm taking off today. I'm in a deep sleep.

132
00:10:56.649 --> 00:10:59.749
Don't knock on the door. Don't wake me up.

133
00:11:31.820 --> 00:11:35.190
Does Hyuk know that she's Baek Seung Gi's daughter?

134
00:11:36.419 --> 00:11:37.789
He didn't at first.

135
00:11:38.659 --> 00:11:40.320
Gosh, that jerk.

136
00:11:40.519 --> 00:11:41.789
There are so many other women.

137
00:11:43.060 --> 00:11:45.799
How could he stay close with the betrayer's daughter?

138
00:11:47.759 --> 00:11:48.799
Is there anything...

139
00:11:49.299 --> 00:11:50.700
that I need to know?

140
00:11:51.639 --> 00:11:53.570
If there is, please tell me.

141
00:11:54.240 --> 00:11:55.370
There's nothing more to know.

142
00:11:56.240 --> 00:11:57.740
You should talk to him.

143
00:11:58.210 --> 00:11:59.679
Make him break up with her.

144
00:12:00.710 --> 00:12:04.009
Tell him that if he ignores my words again, I won't...

145
00:12:06.749 --> 00:12:08.289
spare his life.

146
00:12:09.749 --> 00:12:10.820
Do you understand?

147
00:12:12.060 --> 00:12:13.060
Yes, sir.

148
00:12:32.909 --> 00:12:34.179
June's mom?

149
00:13:05.179 --> 00:13:06.779
Mr. Kim, take care of this.

150
00:13:07.080 --> 00:13:08.879
Yes, just keep doing it.

151
00:13:10.779 --> 00:13:11.779
What?

152
00:13:14.120 --> 00:13:15.850
- About what I told you... - Yes.

153
00:13:16.049 --> 00:13:18.460
- Yes. - I have something to ask you...

154
00:13:28.570 --> 00:13:30.100
Let's just say I understand...

155
00:13:31.200 --> 00:13:34.070
what happened to June's father. He was a lacking person.

156
00:13:35.110 --> 00:13:38.139
But why would you hurt June too?

157
00:13:40.679 --> 00:13:41.710
I know...

158
00:13:42.350 --> 00:13:44.149
what you did to my husband.

159
00:13:44.850 --> 00:13:47.779
How dare you speak of bribery in front of my daughter?

160
00:13:50.519 --> 00:13:51.720
If you talk about bribery...

161
00:13:52.560 --> 00:13:54.659
and hurt June again,

162
00:13:55.659 --> 00:13:56.659
I will...

163
00:13:57.190 --> 00:14:00.029
no longer stay still, Mr. Seol.

164
00:14:02.730 --> 00:14:03.769
If you don't want to...

165
00:14:04.799 --> 00:14:07.769
bring up the Gangsu Chicken incident and cause trouble,

166
00:14:08.810 --> 00:14:10.940
don't make my daughter suffer anymore.

167
00:14:15.580 --> 00:14:16.649
Shouldn't we...

168
00:14:18.049 --> 00:14:19.879
redress what happened then?

169
00:14:30.330 --> 00:14:31.399
Do you think...

170
00:14:31.929 --> 00:14:33.600
you have the right to say such a thing?

171
00:14:39.639 --> 00:14:40.700
Take this...

172
00:14:41.139 --> 00:14:45.080
and stop making objections regarding the oil issue, okay?

173
00:14:46.139 --> 00:14:47.240
The chairman...

174
00:14:48.610 --> 00:14:50.279
has his eyes on you.

175
00:14:50.580 --> 00:14:52.179
So you'd better watch out.

176
00:15:04.360 --> 00:15:05.360
Goodness.

177
00:15:06.060 --> 00:15:07.100
(Yetteo Chicken)

178
00:15:28.249 --> 00:15:29.590
We delivered the message.

179
00:16:11.529 --> 00:16:12.560
What are you doing?

180
00:16:13.159 --> 00:16:14.429
Cleaning.

181
00:16:15.029 --> 00:16:16.100
Cleaning?

182
00:16:16.529 --> 00:16:18.769
I was cleaning...

183
00:16:18.769 --> 00:16:21.039
and Hyuk asked me...

184
00:16:21.440 --> 00:16:23.139
if there was anything he could help.

185
00:16:23.440 --> 00:16:25.110
I said it was okay,

186
00:16:25.210 --> 00:16:27.610
but then my knees hurt, so we were taking a rest for a second.

187
00:16:50.970 --> 00:16:52.070
(Executive Director's Office)

188
00:17:14.590 --> 00:17:15.590
Hey.

189
00:17:15.790 --> 00:17:17.659
Why did June's mom come out from Mr. Seol's office?

190
00:17:20.030 --> 00:17:21.169
I'll tell you later.

191
00:17:22.570 --> 00:17:23.570
Hey.

192
00:17:25.570 --> 00:17:28.239
The chairman called me in this morning.

193
00:17:29.540 --> 00:17:31.909
He wants you to end things with June.

194
00:17:36.179 --> 00:17:39.080
I think your brother reported him about June's dad.

195
00:17:40.780 --> 00:17:41.850
I told you...

196
00:17:42.550 --> 00:17:44.120
not to ignore your brother's warning.

197
00:18:10.209 --> 00:18:15.090
(I'm having a deep sleep at the moment. Don't knock the door.)

198
00:18:20.459 --> 00:18:22.429
I came to make some side dishes for you.

199
00:18:22.429 --> 00:18:23.860
Open the door.

200
00:18:33.969 --> 00:18:35.709
Your dad isn't that kind of a person.

201
00:18:36.540 --> 00:18:37.570
Bribery?

202
00:18:37.770 --> 00:18:39.540
That doesn't make sense at all.

203
00:18:40.879 --> 00:18:43.280
If he had been the type to care only about his interest,

204
00:18:43.780 --> 00:18:45.120
he wouldn't have died like that.

205
00:18:46.320 --> 00:18:49.219
So June, trust your dad.

206
00:18:49.520 --> 00:18:50.590
He is not...

207
00:18:51.189 --> 00:18:52.760
that kind of a person.

208
00:18:57.530 --> 00:18:59.560
(I'm having a deep sleep at the moment. Don't knock the door.)

209
00:19:05.639 --> 00:19:07.500
I'll leave these in front of the door.

210
00:19:08.909 --> 00:19:11.139
Put them in the fridge before they go bad.

211
00:19:14.080 --> 00:19:15.510
I'll come back again...

212
00:19:17.250 --> 00:19:18.550
when you feel like talking.

213
00:19:31.199 --> 00:19:32.229
Mom.

214
00:19:49.780 --> 00:19:50.850
I know.

215
00:19:52.879 --> 00:19:54.790
I know what you're thinking, but it's not true.

216
00:19:56.649 --> 00:19:58.760
There's no one as good as your dad.

217
00:19:59.989 --> 00:20:01.020
I guarantee.

218
00:21:55.709 --> 00:21:56.770
What's up?

219
00:21:57.370 --> 00:21:58.679
You really have guts for this.

220
00:22:00.239 --> 00:22:01.709
For how many years have you been doing this every day?

221
00:22:03.010 --> 00:22:04.149
About 11 years.

222
00:22:04.750 --> 00:22:05.780
11 years.

223
00:22:07.350 --> 00:22:08.719
So it's since that incident.

224
00:22:15.489 --> 00:22:16.489
What's your point?

225
00:22:16.590 --> 00:22:17.929
June is the person I like.

226
00:22:19.760 --> 00:22:21.429
I won't stay still...

227
00:22:21.429 --> 00:22:23.699
if you threaten her with such a dirty trick one more time.

228
00:22:24.870 --> 00:22:25.870
What?

229
00:22:25.870 --> 00:22:29.770
And stop ratting on stuff to Dad.

230
00:22:30.909 --> 00:22:32.879
Don't you think you're too old for that?

231
00:22:34.409 --> 00:22:35.610
Why this punk...

232
00:22:35.709 --> 00:22:37.250
Don't do it ever again.

233
00:22:44.790 --> 00:22:45.790
Bye.

234
00:24:48.810 --> 00:24:50.050
Why are you here again?

235
00:24:50.350 --> 00:24:53.879
I thought about it, and what you told me doesn't make sense.

236
00:24:55.449 --> 00:24:56.850
Are you hiding something from me?

237
00:24:59.760 --> 00:25:00.989
No, I'm not.

238
00:25:01.429 --> 00:25:02.929
About my dad receiving bribes.

239
00:25:04.229 --> 00:25:07.830
If that's all you can tell me, what are the things you can't tell?

240
00:25:08.270 --> 00:25:10.030
There isn't anything like that.

241
00:25:12.040 --> 00:25:13.939
Yes, there is. There's something.

242
00:25:14.239 --> 00:25:16.370
Please tell me the truth, Mr. Jang.

243
00:25:16.840 --> 00:25:18.780
- Gosh, seriously. - Mr. Jang!

244
00:25:19.209 --> 00:25:20.280
Mr. Jang.

245
00:25:21.179 --> 00:25:23.810
Mr. Jang, please tell me. Mr. Jang!

246
00:25:24.879 --> 00:25:27.580
I'm sorry. You'd better go.

247
00:25:29.090 --> 00:25:30.689
I know you're distressed too.

248
00:25:31.290 --> 00:25:32.790
That's why you should tell me.

249
00:25:33.959 --> 00:25:36.889
I'll wait right here until you tell me the truth.

250
00:25:37.429 --> 00:25:39.800
Mr. Jang. Mr. Jang!

251
00:25:56.010 --> 00:25:59.250
What are you doing now? Do you know what time it is?

252
00:26:00.020 --> 00:26:03.290
I'm sorry. It's not that I didn't come to work.

253
00:26:03.949 --> 00:26:06.389
I came to work, but something urgent came up, so...

254
00:26:06.790 --> 00:26:09.030
You're an intern, and you are not doing what you have to do.

255
00:26:09.129 --> 00:26:10.189
You're always away from your desk.

256
00:26:10.330 --> 00:26:11.959
- You get smart with me... - Excuse me.

257
00:26:12.800 --> 00:26:14.629
It's an important call. Wait a minute.

258
00:26:15.830 --> 00:26:16.870
Yes, Mr. Jang.

259
00:26:17.169 --> 00:26:18.939
Gosh, the world has become much easier to live in.

260
00:26:19.040 --> 00:26:22.010
You can answer the phone while your boss is talking. It's gotten better.

261
00:26:22.439 --> 00:26:23.639
What? June?

262
00:26:25.209 --> 00:26:27.879
Yes, I get it. I'll be there soon.

263
00:26:28.409 --> 00:26:29.610
Where are you going?

264
00:26:29.709 --> 00:26:32.379
Mr. Jang called me urgently. I have to go.

265
00:26:32.520 --> 00:26:34.280
I'll be right back. Thank you.

266
00:26:34.620 --> 00:26:35.620
Well, it's...

267
00:26:36.419 --> 00:26:39.760
The third-generation guy works at this company so freely.

268
00:26:40.790 --> 00:26:43.330
It's just like the tail wagging the dog, isn't it?

269
00:26:44.830 --> 00:26:46.929
I called you because I think she may faint.

270
00:26:48.070 --> 00:26:49.330
