00:49:09.422 --> 00:49:10.893
I told you I can't.

553
00:49:13.763 --> 00:49:14.802
Mr. Jang,

554
00:49:16.032 --> 00:49:17.732
you know how I helped you...

555
00:49:18.802 --> 00:49:19.902
with your cupbap.

556
00:49:20.933 --> 00:49:22.143
I went against my father...

557
00:49:23.273 --> 00:49:24.342
to make it work.

558
00:49:26.842 --> 00:49:28.143
I don't think like my father.

559
00:49:28.782 --> 00:49:30.243
If something has been wronged,

560
00:49:30.712 --> 00:49:33.683
I think that now is still not late to make it right.

561
00:49:35.853 --> 00:49:38.123
Please give me a chance to do that, Mr. Jang.

562
00:49:45.862 --> 00:49:47.902
Maybe, this could be the last chance...

563
00:49:49.203 --> 00:49:51.273
to get rid of your guilt.

564
00:49:57.402 --> 00:49:59.212
Baek Seung Gi was kicked out.

565
00:50:01.112 --> 00:50:02.982
He wanted to get rid of the custom...

566
00:50:03.643 --> 00:50:04.982
of receiving bribes from subcontractors.

567
00:50:06.282 --> 00:50:07.453
So he brought up...

568
00:50:08.482 --> 00:50:10.052
the issue to the company...

569
00:50:11.252 --> 00:50:12.793
and people started discussing about it...

570
00:50:14.052 --> 00:50:15.322
when the superiors stopped him.

571
00:50:17.623 --> 00:50:18.692
The superiors?

572
00:50:19.663 --> 00:50:21.462
If this issue were to be brought up,

573
00:50:22.132 --> 00:50:24.132
many would've gotten hurt.

574
00:50:26.232 --> 00:50:29.672
Rather than reconstructing the company just to break an old custom,

575
00:50:30.172 --> 00:50:32.842
they decided that it'd be easier...

576
00:50:33.743 --> 00:50:35.543
to get rid of him.

577
00:50:37.442 --> 00:50:38.482
So?

578
00:50:41.223 --> 00:50:42.882
They say that a cornered stone meets the mason's chisel.

579
00:50:44.223 --> 00:50:45.223
One day,

580
00:50:46.192 --> 00:50:49.422
the chairman ordered me directly...

581
00:50:50.163 --> 00:50:53.192
to testify falsely...

582
00:50:55.032 --> 00:50:56.933
that I bribed Baek Seung Gi...

583
00:50:57.502 --> 00:50:58.703
regularly.

584
00:51:01.043 --> 00:51:02.172
He said if I didn't,

585
00:51:03.973 --> 00:51:06.043
he would cancel the contract with my factory.

586
00:51:09.382 --> 00:51:10.442
That's how...

587
00:51:10.842 --> 00:51:14.623
I betrayed Baek Seung Gi.

588
00:51:18.822 --> 00:51:20.092
So that I could live.

589
00:51:22.123 --> 00:51:25.862
He never received bribes.

590
00:51:27.393 --> 00:51:28.402
Rather,

591
00:51:29.263 --> 00:51:31.232
whenever our contract was in danger of being cancelled...

592
00:51:32.203 --> 00:51:34.802
he would argue with his superiors saying that...

593
00:51:35.143 --> 00:51:37.572
he couldn't betray a partner he'd been working for a long time.

594
00:51:38.942 --> 00:51:39.973
I...

595
00:51:41.913 --> 00:51:42.982
I...

596
00:51:44.313 --> 00:51:45.752
I did that to save myself.

597
00:51:52.652 --> 00:51:53.692
I'm sorry.

598
00:51:55.362 --> 00:51:56.523
I'm truly sorry.

599
00:51:58.862 --> 00:51:59.862
I...

600
00:52:00.862 --> 00:52:02.632
I feel ashamed to see you.

601
00:52:16.083 --> 00:52:17.712
(Manager Baek Seung Gi)

602
00:52:33.163 --> 00:52:35.302
(Manager Baek Seung Gi)

603
00:53:06.962 --> 00:53:08.802
He took all the blame...

604
00:53:09.002 --> 00:53:10.263
and left the company.

605
00:53:11.402 --> 00:53:13.873
He was falsely charged of bribery with dishonor.

606
00:53:21.813 --> 00:53:23.712
Who was behind all this?

607
00:53:28.953 --> 00:53:30.083
Was it my dad?

608
00:54:13.632 --> 00:54:14.703
Are you done talking with him?

609
00:54:15.663 --> 00:54:16.663
Yes.

610
00:54:16.933 --> 00:54:18.032
Did you hear...

611
00:54:19.002 --> 00:54:20.132
everything you wanted to hear?

612
00:54:22.273 --> 00:54:23.273
Yes.

613
00:54:29.513 --> 00:54:30.712
How did you know?

614
00:54:32.453 --> 00:54:33.453
I mean...

615
00:54:35.353 --> 00:54:37.623
Since when did you know about my dad?

616
00:54:38.293 --> 00:54:39.353
The same day as you.

617
00:54:40.652 --> 00:54:41.822
Did you hear it from your brother?

618
00:54:42.793 --> 00:54:43.793
Yes.

619
00:54:44.993 --> 00:54:45.993
Then...

620
00:54:47.362 --> 00:54:51.502
You must've heard that I was using you.

621
00:54:53.103 --> 00:54:54.103
Yes.

622
00:54:54.743 --> 00:54:56.203
Why did you do nothing about it?

623
00:54:58.612 --> 00:55:00.813
What if it's true?

624
00:55:01.482 --> 00:55:02.612
I know you're not.

625
00:55:05.152 --> 00:55:06.152
Even if...

626
00:55:07.552 --> 00:55:09.422
you really are using me,

627
00:55:09.882 --> 00:55:10.982
I can't help it.

628
00:55:12.052 --> 00:55:13.092
This all...

629
00:55:14.322 --> 00:55:16.092
happened because of my dad.

630
00:55:27.402 --> 00:55:28.402
My friend.

631
00:55:33.712 --> 00:55:34.782
My friend.

632
00:55:37.683 --> 00:55:39.083
My friend.

633
00:55:42.752 --> 00:55:43.953
Can I hug you...

634
00:55:48.293 --> 00:55:49.523
as a friend for just once?

635
00:56:17.252 --> 00:56:18.353
Thank you.

636
00:56:21.592 --> 00:56:23.763
I was able to hear that my dad was falsely accused...

637
00:56:25.962 --> 00:56:27.132
thanks to you.

638
00:56:37.873 --> 00:56:40.543
June, do you know?

639
00:56:41.942 --> 00:56:44.453
This is only the beginning.

640
00:57:04.560 --> 00:57:06.521
- Hi. - Are you out of your mind?

641
00:57:06.821 --> 00:57:08.791
Why are you in this together when you're supposed to stop her?

642
00:57:09.291 --> 00:57:10.330
Why should I stop her?

643
00:57:10.691 --> 00:57:12.501
I helped her hear what she wanted to hear.

644
00:57:12.901 --> 00:57:14.100
Is it that wrong?

645
00:57:14.301 --> 00:57:15.830
Don't you see what's going on?

646
00:57:16.030 --> 00:57:18.470
Your brother's taken measures at the mention of June's dad's name.

647
00:57:18.571 --> 00:57:20.801
Now, the chairman wants you to end things with June.

648
00:57:23.810 --> 00:57:25.981
That's why I don't understand it all the more.

649
00:57:27.041 --> 00:57:28.780
Don't you think they're hiding something behind?

650
00:57:29.711 --> 00:57:31.010
What will you do if they are?

651
00:57:31.120 --> 00:57:33.080
- I'll reveal it. - You should cover it.

652
00:57:35.921 --> 00:57:36.921
Je Hoon.

653
00:57:38.060 --> 00:57:39.120
What's your dream?

654
00:57:40.821 --> 00:57:42.260
Why are you asking about my dream all of a sudden?

655
00:57:42.560 --> 00:57:43.791
Then let me ask you again.

656
00:57:45.060 --> 00:57:46.861
What do you want to do in this company?

657
00:57:49.301 --> 00:57:50.430
Do you like this company?

658
00:57:50.631 --> 00:57:52.140
Are you happy working at Gangsu Group?

659
00:57:55.771 --> 00:57:57.370
No one feels happy working at a company.

660
00:57:57.780 --> 00:57:59.180
Can't you be?

661
00:58:00.211 --> 00:58:01.280
Tell me.

662
00:58:01.551 --> 00:58:02.751
For you to be happy,

663
00:58:03.280 --> 00:58:05.080
how should this company change?

664
00:58:06.421 --> 00:58:09.120
Why? Will you sing and dance again to bring a change?

665
00:58:09.691 --> 00:58:11.321
The cleaners' employment and the subcontractor issue...

666
00:58:11.861 --> 00:58:13.990
didn't get settled because of you.

667
00:58:14.091 --> 00:58:15.160
Don't be mistaken.

668
00:58:15.560 --> 00:58:17.961
To be exact, they got settled because you're the chairman's son.

669
00:58:18.260 --> 00:58:19.301
Tell me about it.

670
00:58:20.231 --> 00:58:22.171
That's why I'm wondering...

671
00:58:22.271 --> 00:58:24.740
if there's anything more to change while I'm still the chairman's son.

672
00:58:26.640 --> 00:58:28.970
- What? - I can prove that my dad's wrong...

673
00:58:29.441 --> 00:58:31.941
if things get better by changing.

674
00:58:33.310 --> 00:58:35.780
What are you thinking?

675
00:58:37.010 --> 00:58:38.821
Don't you want to see...

676
00:58:39.751 --> 00:58:41.450
my dad admitting his fault for once?

677
00:58:41.850 --> 00:58:43.051
I'm dying to see.

678
00:59:13.921 --> 00:59:16.521
What happened to our promotional partner?

679
00:59:16.521 --> 00:59:18.421
- Check here. - I called them and they're not...

680
00:59:18.421 --> 00:59:20.220
No, we need to get this done quickly.

681
00:59:20.421 --> 00:59:23.260
Come here, Hyun Joo. Hurry.

682
00:59:23.430 --> 00:59:25.100
Because we're afraid of the upper management.

683
00:59:25.801 --> 00:59:27.870
If we don't make good outcomes, we can't get promoted.

684
00:59:28.530 --> 00:59:29.600
Then...

685
00:59:30.001 --> 00:59:31.841
we'll get kicked out of the company in a split second.

686
00:59:32.970 --> 00:59:35.071
You don't share what you have when you do business.

687
00:59:35.271 --> 00:59:37.310
The weak are the prey of the strong. Don't you get it, you punk?

688
00:59:38.041 --> 00:59:41.481
If you don't eat, you get eaten. That's the way it is.

689
00:59:46.051 --> 00:59:47.651
No matter how much loyal you are to a company,

690
00:59:48.220 --> 00:59:50.450
you get thrown away like consumable goods in a second.

691
00:59:51.591 --> 00:59:53.361
It's the destiny of salarymen.

692
00:59:58.461 --> 00:59:59.501
What do you...

693
01:00:00.361 --> 01:00:01.600
plan to do now?

694
01:00:04.171 --> 01:00:05.541
(Resume)

695
01:00:06.370 --> 01:00:07.600
(Resume)

696
01:00:09.671 --> 01:00:11.441
Is the information right? My contact number...

697
01:00:11.441 --> 01:00:12.910
It's fine as long as I wrote my contact number right.

698
01:00:13.211 --> 01:00:15.711
By the way, what are you going to use these for?

699
01:00:16.280 --> 01:00:17.821
You're not going to use them for something weird, are you?

700
01:00:18.021 --> 01:00:19.950
I have a bad feeling about this.

701
01:00:20.551 --> 01:00:21.551
Please don't.

702
01:00:21.950 --> 01:00:23.151
I'll use them for a good purpose.

703
01:00:52.481 --> 01:00:53.881
You heard from Je Hoon, right?

704
01:00:55.251 --> 01:00:56.791
- Yes, Dad. - So?

705
01:00:57.890 --> 01:00:59.791
Did you end things with June?

706
01:01:01.191 --> 01:01:02.461
Before that, I'm curious about something.

707
01:01:03.830 --> 01:01:07.830
Why did you frame an innocent man and kick him out of the company?

708
01:01:09.071 --> 01:01:10.171
Who said...

709
01:01:10.571 --> 01:01:12.100
that Baek Seung Gi didn't do anything wrong?

710
01:01:12.200 --> 01:01:13.200
What did he do wrong?

711
01:01:14.941 --> 01:01:16.671
He pointed a sword at the company management...

712
01:01:17.211 --> 01:01:19.211
with a naive sense of ambition.

713
01:01:21.410 --> 01:01:23.751
You don't run a company with a sense of justice.

714
01:01:23.751 --> 01:01:25.280
A company must make profits.

715
01:01:27.821 --> 01:01:29.691
It needs people in order to make profits.

716
01:01:29.990 --> 01:01:33.390
I couldn't shake the entire company for the sake of Baek Seung Gi.

717
01:01:35.691 --> 01:01:36.691
In the end,

718
01:01:37.291 --> 01:01:39.600
you chose money over a person.

719
01:01:41.700 --> 01:01:43.700
Sometimes, you need a small sacrifice...

720
01:01:44.330 --> 01:01:45.740
for the greater good.

721
01:01:46.200 --> 01:01:47.200
For who?

722
01:01:47.401 --> 01:01:49.410
For every member in the company.

723
01:01:49.611 --> 01:01:50.711
Not for you, Dad?

724
01:01:50.910 --> 01:01:52.080
The company is me.

725
01:01:57.381 --> 01:01:58.421
Okay.

726
01:01:59.350 --> 01:02:02.321
Father, do you remember the reward last time?

727
01:02:03.720 --> 01:02:04.791
Reward?

728
01:02:05.560 --> 01:02:08.961
You didn't forget about it, did you?

729
01:02:09.490 --> 01:02:12.131
You mentioned it after receiving the presidential award.

730
01:02:12.430 --> 01:02:15.001
I didn't forget about it. What do you want me to do?

731
01:02:15.671 --> 01:02:18.571
Do you need a house? Should I buy you a car?

732
01:02:20.001 --> 01:02:22.370
These are the hidden contributors behind the award.

733
01:02:24.881 --> 01:02:27.910
Please employ these people to the planning team.

734
01:02:29.410 --> 01:02:32.180
- Is that it? - Yes, that's it.

735
01:02:40.390 --> 01:02:42.291
(Lee Tae Kyung's Resume)

736
01:02:46.501 --> 01:02:48.930
(An Mi Yeon's Resume)

737
01:02:53.571 --> 01:02:56.140
(Kim Ki Seob's Resume)

738
01:03:00.140 --> 01:03:03.251
I trust you to employ them. I'm leaving.

739
01:03:04.751 --> 01:03:05.821
Why won't you answer me?

740
01:03:06.981 --> 01:03:09.921
Did you end the relationship with that girl?

741
01:03:14.191 --> 01:03:16.191
June and I are just friends.

742
01:03:17.060 --> 01:03:19.501
She's my friend.

743
01:03:20.060 --> 01:03:22.271
She's my friend.

744
01:03:23.700 --> 01:03:25.171
Don't worry.

745
01:03:40.321 --> 01:03:44.691
I think Hyuk's crossing the line because he's in love with that girl.

746
01:03:47.260 --> 01:03:48.291
What do you mean?

747
01:04:11.450 --> 01:04:12.950
We have to get rid of her from the company...

748
01:04:13.751 --> 01:04:15.191
before Hyuk causes trouble again.

749
01:04:29.430 --> 01:04:31.771
(Kim Ki Seob's Resume)

750
01:04:39.810 --> 01:04:42.651
Here's a cup of delicious americano.

751
01:04:42.850 --> 01:04:43.950
Thank you.

752
01:04:47.720 --> 01:04:50.751
June, you're even good at making coffee. It's better than any cafe.

753
01:04:51.691 --> 01:04:53.660
You're off duty today. Didn't you go anywhere?

754
01:04:54.060 --> 01:04:56.490
I want to ask you something about Kwon Je Hoon.

755
01:04:57.430 --> 01:04:58.501
What about him?

756
01:04:59.830 --> 01:05:01.071
Does he have a girlfriend?

757
01:05:03.700 --> 01:05:04.801
I'm not sure.

758
01:05:06.071 --> 01:05:07.441
I think he doesn't have one.

759
01:05:08.071 --> 01:05:09.140
Why?

760
01:05:09.941 --> 01:05:12.740
Actually, last night...

761
01:05:13.611 --> 01:05:17.280
I was struggling because my heel got stuck in a manhole cover.

762
01:05:17.921 --> 01:05:19.381
He suddenly appeared...

763
01:05:19.881 --> 01:05:21.720
and took it out with his hands.

764
01:05:22.751 --> 01:05:23.791
Je Hoon did that?

765
01:05:25.760 --> 01:05:26.760
I can't believe that.

766
01:05:27.760 --> 01:05:29.791
He's not nice to women.

767
01:05:29.990 --> 01:05:31.030
Right?

768
01:05:31.731 --> 01:05:34.001
I didn't think he was nice.

769
01:05:35.370 --> 01:05:37.501
That's why I felt...

770
01:05:38.341 --> 01:05:39.341
strange.

771
01:05:40.970 --> 01:05:44.841
Last time, he suddenly gave me some porridge.

772
01:05:45.881 --> 01:05:46.881
Porridge?

773
01:05:47.611 --> 01:05:48.910
He gave it to you?

774
01:05:49.481 --> 01:05:50.580
Do you think...

775
01:05:52.251 --> 01:05:53.421
he likes me?

776
01:05:56.321 --> 01:05:58.191
What do you think?

777
01:05:58.890 --> 01:06:01.361
You should know since you've known him for a long time.

778
01:06:03.030 --> 01:06:04.060
What about you?

779
01:06:06.160 --> 01:06:07.901
Aren't your feelings more important?

780
01:06:09.030 --> 01:06:10.071
What?

781
01:06:10.901 --> 01:06:12.100
I guess...

782
01:06:13.640 --> 01:06:17.270
How could you ask such a thing so directly? I'm embarrassed.

783
01:06:19.511 --> 01:06:21.610
Actually...

784
01:06:23.410 --> 01:06:24.480
Je Hoon.

785
01:06:34.431 --> 01:06:35.490
Was...

786
01:06:36.061 --> 01:06:37.291
Hyuk up here?

787
01:06:38.001 --> 01:06:39.501
He wasn't here.

788
01:06:44.001 --> 01:06:45.740
Where did he go? He won't even pick up the phone.

789
01:06:53.110 --> 01:06:54.181
What should I do?

790
01:06:55.181 --> 01:06:56.681
Did he hear everything?

791
01:06:57.950 --> 01:06:59.820
He's slow, so he wouldn't have heard anything.

792
01:07:18.001 --> 01:07:19.041
I'm sorry.

793
01:07:21.841 --> 01:07:22.841
Excuse me.

794
01:07:28.980 --> 01:07:30.051
Do you want this?

795
01:07:31.881 --> 01:07:32.881
What?

796
01:07:59.110 --> 01:08:01.110
Je Hoon, are you home?

797
01:08:04.011 --> 01:08:06.150
No matter how tired you are, you should change before you sleep.

798
01:08:06.650 --> 01:08:07.820
You'll catch a cold.

799
01:08:09.620 --> 01:08:11.061
Don't talk to me.

800
01:08:11.391 --> 01:08:12.421
Okay.

801
01:08:17.561 --> 01:08:20.101
(Related Data of G Chicken)

802
01:08:30.011 --> 01:08:31.041
Hyuk,

803
01:08:32.881 --> 01:08:34.110
how serious are you?

804
01:08:34.580 --> 01:08:35.580
What do you mean?

805
01:08:37.450 --> 01:08:38.650
What you told me earlier.

806
01:08:40.921 --> 01:08:42.921
Why? Are you curious?

807
01:08:43.851 --> 01:08:47.091
Look forward to tomorrow morning. You're going to be really surprised.

808
01:09:32.301 --> 01:09:36.070
I am Kim Ki Seob, and I'll be working here in the planning team.

809
01:09:36.610 --> 01:09:37.711
I'll work hard.

810
01:09:47.891 --> 01:09:48.950
Bravo.

811
01:09:49.891 --> 01:09:51.120
Did you make Hyuk do it?

812
01:09:52.160 --> 01:09:53.221
Do what?

813
01:09:53.490 --> 01:09:54.490
Is there something wrong?

814
01:09:54.761 --> 01:09:55.761
Don't you know?

815
01:09:57.030 --> 01:09:58.761
Did Hyuk plan that all by himself?

816
01:09:58.961 --> 01:10:00.631
What did he do?

817
01:10:01.030 --> 01:10:02.131
I don't understand.

818
01:10:02.801 --> 01:10:04.440
The planning team is in an uproar.

819
01:10:05.070 --> 01:10:06.101
Why?

820
01:10:11.740 --> 01:10:12.811
June.

821
01:10:24.091 --> 01:10:25.091
Mr. Kim?

822
01:10:28.490 --> 01:10:30.961
Hyuk brought him to the planning team.

823
01:10:36.700 --> 01:10:38.101
He says he wants to change the company.

824
01:10:38.971 --> 01:10:41.711
Don't you know what he's thinking?

825
01:10:42.141 --> 01:10:43.171
I don't know.

826
